Pause work on a Linear issue.

## Usage

```
/pause-linear
/pause-linear <reason>
```

## Description

Use this command when you need to pause work on an issue without it being blocked. This is different from `/get-feedback-linear` or `/blocked-linear` - you're simply switching priorities or taking a break.

Perfect for:
- Higher priority work came up
- End of day / end of sprint
- Switching context to another issue
- Taking a break or vacation
- Waiting for non-blocking dependency

